cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.NE 

This paper deals with unsupervised learning and model drift, which are topics commonly studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new metric for evaluating distances between Mapper graphs, which involves topological data analysis (cs.DS) and network analysis (cs.SI). The use of optimal transport in the metric also suggests a potential connection to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the application of the metric to anomaly detection in dynamic graphs involves neural networks (cs.NE).
